Also competed in track and field (shot put) as a Georgia prep. Verbally committed to Virginia Tech but failed to qualify and attended Hargrave Military Academy (Va.) in 2006. Changed his commitment to South Carolina and started 10-of-12 games played in '07, recording 39 tackles, 3½ for loss and three sacks with a pass batted down. Did not start against Louisiana-Lafayette or Kentucky. Broke his right hand in July '08 while working as a bouncer. In the fall, started 12-of-13 games (gave way to 3-4 alignment against Kentucky) and tallied 22-1½-1½ with two batted passes. Was arrested in February '09 for marijuana possession and served a three-game suspension. On the season, started all 10 games in which he played and notched 45-4-0. Played in all 14 contests in '10, starting 13 at defensive tackle, and posted 41-5-2. Did not start the season opener against Southern Mississippi after fracturing his left hand during preseason camp.
